gomodel:SYNGO_2016  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Localization of the fetal nACHR subunit epsylon to motor endplates (stained with alpha-BTX) is shown with an anti-epsilon anitbody. The localization of the epsilon-containing nACHR under study is without a single doubt in the postsynaptic specialization membrane.\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Delayed expression of the AChR ε-subunit in leg muscles of the MyoD-/- mice\"" ;
